#! <SUBDOCUMENTS>
#! <SUBDOCUMENT
#!   NAME="BRepSolidBoundaryCreator.Beta"
#!   ARCGIS_COMPATIBILITY=""
#!   CATEGORY="3D"
#!   DESCRIPTION="&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;Creates a planar surface representing the orthogonal projection of the source surface, and a ring-shaped vertical sidewall surface that bridges between the boundaries of the planar surface and the source surface. The resulting surfaces can be used to build a boundary representation solid (IFMEBRepSolid). &lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;This transformer accepts features having a surface geometry except aggregate and multi-surface. If the input feature geometry is not acceptable, it will be output via the &amp;lt;Rejected&amp;gt; port. &lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;Note: This transformer is a tech preview regarding surface manipulation with Python FME Objects API. It may be removed from the FME Hub if a regular transformer having a functionality equivalent to this transformer would be introduced in the future.&lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; font-weight:600; color:#0000ff;&quot;&gt;Usage Note&lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;This transformer assumes that the source surface represents a single consecutive shape oriented to Z positive direction, and the boundary of the source surface is equal to the boundary of the orthogonal projection (i.e. the source surface is NOT folded). Otherwise, the translation could be aborted with an error or the resulting surfaces may not form a topologically clean solid. &lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;You can transform an aggregate of surfaces which are output from this transformer into a boundary representation solid (IFMEBrepSolid) or a composite surface (IFMECompositeSurface), using an Aggregator and a GeometryCoercer transformer (Geometry Type: fme_brep_solid or fme_composite_surface).&lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; font-weight:600; color:#0000ff;&quot;&gt;Output Ports &lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#005500;&quot;&gt;Top&lt;/span&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;: &lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;If the elevation which is specified through the &quot;Planar Surface Elevation&quot; parameter is less than the MINIMUM Z of the source surface, the source surface will be output via this port without any transformation. If the specified elevation is greater than the MAXIMUM Z of the source surface, a planar surface representing the orthogonal projection of the source surface will be output via this port.&lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#005500;&quot;&gt;Side&lt;/span&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;A composite surface forming a ring-shaped vertical sidewall that bridges between the boundaries of the Top surface and the Bottom surface will be output via this port.&lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#005500;&quot;&gt;Bottom&lt;/span&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;span style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;If the elevation which is specified through the &quot;Planar Surface Elevation&quot; parameter is less than the MINIMUM Z of the source surface, the planar surface representing the orthogonal projection of the source surface will be output via this port. If the specified elevation is greater than the MAXIMUM Z of the source surface, the source surface whose orientation is reversed will be output via this port. &lt;/span&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;"
